Post Cabinet Media briefing by Minister in the Presidency Jackson Mthembu on 08 August 2019 JOHANNESBURG - Minister In Presidency Jackson Jackson Mthembu has thanked South Africans who are staying at home. Mthembu was speaking during the National Command Council update on the lockdown on Saturday. He also thanked the country’s health workers, security forces, traditional and church leaders for their role in fighting the spread of the coronavirus. READ: First coronavirus death confirmed in SA "We once again want to thank all people of South Africa. Particularly those who are heeding the call to stay at home", he said. South Africa has begun a 21-day national lockdown in a bid to curb the spread of the virus. As it stands, there are nearly 600,000 infections and more than 27,000 deaths worldwide. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.